  "description": "A circular arrangement of approximately fifteen snail shells is displayed on a light beige surface. The shells vary in color, ranging from pale cream and white to shades of brown and grey. Each shell exhibits a spiraled, conical shape, with noticeable ridges and textures. Some shells have darker bands or patterns. The shells are positioned with their openings facing outwards, creating a radial pattern. The background is a uniform, slightly textured beige, providing a neutral backdrop for the shells. There is a small speck of orange in the bottom left corner.",
